      "title": "The Resembling Adjective (الصفة المشبهة)",
      "titleArabic": "الصفة المشبهة",
      "content": [
        "The resembling adjective (الصفة المشبهة) is derived from intransitive verbs and describes permanent qualities or characteristics.",
        "Unlike the active participle which describes temporary states, the resembling adjective indicates inherent, lasting qualities."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Derived mainly from Form I intransitive verbs",
        "Indicates permanent qualities (not temporary actions)",
        "Multiple patterns: فَعِيل، فَعَل، فَعْل، فُعَال، أَفْعَل",
        "Resembles the active participle in function but differs in meaning"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "كَرِيمٌ", "english": "generous (permanent trait)" },
        { "arabic": "شُجَاعٌ", "english": "brave (permanent trait)" },
        { "arabic": "حَسَنٌ", "english": "good / beautiful" },
        { "arabic": "صَعْبٌ", "english": "difficult" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "الأوزان الشائعة",
      "content": [
        "The resembling adjective follows several patterns, each indicating a particular type of permanent quality.",
        "These adjectives can take the regular adjective agreement rules for gender and number."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فَعِيل: كَرِيم، عَظِيم، جَمِيل (noble, great, beautiful)",
        "فَعَل: حَسَن، بَطَل (good, hero)",
        "فَعْل: صَعْب، سَهْل (difficult, easy)",
        "فُعَال: شُجَاع، طُوَال (brave, tall)",
        "أَفْعَل: أَحْمَر، أَعْرَج (red, lame)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "هُوَ رَجُلٌ كَرِيمٌ", "english": "He is a generous man" },
